# AI Optimization Checklist
**Complete Guide to Optimizing Your Digital Presence for AI Platforms**

Last Updated: November 2025

---

## How to Use This Checklist

- Print this checklist or save it digitally
- Check off items as you complete them
- Review quarterly to maintain AI optimization
- Prioritize items based on your business goals
- Track completion dates for accountability

---

## 1. Technical Website Optimization

### Core Technical SEO
- [ ] Ensure website is mobile-responsive and passes Google Mobile-Friendly Test
- [ ] Achieve Core Web Vitals targets (LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1)
- [ ] Implement HTTPS security across entire site
- [ ] Create and submit XML sitemap to search engines
- [ ] Optimize robots.txt file for proper crawling
- [ ] Fix all broken links and 404 errors
- [ ] Implement canonical URLs to avoid duplicate content
- [ ] Set up proper URL structure (clear, descriptive, hierarchical)

### Schema Markup Implementation
- [ ] Add Organization schema to homepage
- [ ] Implement Product schema on product pages
- [ ] Add Article schema to blog posts
- [ ] Include FAQ schema on relevant pages
- [ ] Add Review/Rating schema where applicable
- [ ] Implement Breadcrumb schema for navigation
- [ ] Add Person/Author schema for content creators
- [ ] Include LocalBusiness schema (if applicable)
- [ ] Validate all schema markup with Google Rich Results Test
- [ ] Test schema in Schema.org validator

### Page Speed & Performance
- [ ] Compress and optimize all images (WebP format when possible)
- [ ] Minify CSS, JavaScript, and HTML files
- [ ] Enable browser caching
- [ ] Use a Content Delivery Network (CDN)
- [ ] Lazy load images and videos
- [ ] Remove unused CSS and JavaScript
- [ ] Optimize server response time (< 200ms)

