## 2. Content Optimization

### Content Structure
- [ ] Use clear, hierarchical heading structure (H1, H2, H3)
- [ ] Write descriptive, keyword-rich meta titles (50-60 characters)
- [ ] Create compelling meta descriptions (150-160 characters)
- [ ] Include target keywords naturally in first 100 words
- [ ] Use short paragraphs (2-3 sentences maximum)
- [ ] Add bulleted and numbered lists for scannability
- [ ] Include a table of contents for long-form content

### AI-Friendly Content Elements
- [ ] Create FAQ sections answering common questions
- [ ] Write in natural, conversational language
- [ ] Define technical terms and industry jargon
- [ ] Include comparison tables and versus content
- [ ] Add "What is..." definitions for key concepts
- [ ] Create step-by-step how-to guides
- [ ] Include specific data, statistics, and facts
- [ ] Add expert quotes and insights
- [ ] Provide clear, actionable takeaways

### Content Quality & E-E-A-T
- [ ] Add author bylines with credentials
- [ ] Include publication and last updated dates
- [ ] Link to authoritative external sources
- [ ] Cite data sources and research
- [ ] Add internal links to related content
- [ ] Include original images, charts, and diagrams
- [ ] Proofread for grammar and spelling
- [ ] Ensure content is accurate and up-to-date
- [ ] Add expertise indicators (certifications, awards, experience)

